  "text": "The trip lengths ( ) in our data correspond to the actual traveled distances, reported by subjects. Hence, in contrast to check-in data, we do not have to approximate trip lengths by Euclidean displacements (Δr) [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] , which may introduce a bias to the scaling exponent, especially for short trips. This is particularly interesting, since our data features a high resolution, recorded down to the 100m scale.",
